{
  "stem": "14168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I worked on the marketing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I traveled to Latin America, to Japan.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "In the meantime, I heard that one could-- one could study law, I could study law-- I was always interested in the law-- by taking correspondence course-- correspondence courses.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I enrolled with La Salle Extension University in Chicago, and I started studying law.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And after a number of years where I always had my books with me-- I studied nights, I studied weekends, and during trips, I always had my law books.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And we're taking, right now, some very gigantic steps here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I'm just telling you--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I took the California bar, passed it, and went into the practice of law. 1962.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First, I practiced law in the evenings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I drew will for people-- wills for people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did certain things.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then I figured the only way to practice law is to take the jump, which I did, hoping I was-- I felt like the-- the parachutist who hopes that the parachute will open.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, it finally opened shortly before landing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I landed smoothly, and I practiced international law.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I worked for several consulates, foreign clients trying to establish themselves in California and vice versa.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I also work a great deal, do a great deal, in international arbitration.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I'm very much interested in Jewish affairs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Ursula helped me tremendously.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Without her help, take all-- freeing me from all the problems of household, all the decisions, and enabling me to pursue my law studies in addition to making a living-- that was invaluable.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Without her, I wouldn't be where I am right now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She stuck to me in every situation of my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She worked, too.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She worked then as a clerk for a bank.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
